# Phase 35: Premium UI/UX & Engagement Intelligence

This phase expands the premium overhaul to include robust views tracking, automated engagement, and mobile UI optimization for the Creator Studio.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Views Tracking**: I am implementing a `daily_stats` table to track views over time. Existing views will be captured, but historical "day-by-day" data for old videos won't be available immediately.
> **Automatic Engagement**: The "Slow Drip" system will automatically add 1-5 views to videos with low engagement every time the drip is triggered (can be automated via Supabase Cron).

## Proposed Changes

### Database & Analytics
#### [NEW] [daily-stats.sql](file:///C:/GOLive/scripts/daily-stats.sql)
- Create `daily_stats` table to track `views` and `revenue` per day per user.
- Create `drip_global_engagement()` RPC to automate baseline engagement.
- Update `increment_view_count` to also log to `daily_stats`.

### Backend APIs
#### [NEW] [route.ts](file:///C:/GOLive/app/api/studio/analytics/route.ts)
- New endpoint to provide temporal data for views and revenue charts.

### Frontend - Creator Studio
#### [MODIFY] [DashboardClient.tsx](file:///C:/GOLive/app/studio/dashboard/DashboardClient.tsx)
- Integrate Views Velocity chart using Recharts.
- Optimized Mobile layout for stats cards and video management.
- Improved "Engagement" indicator for videos.

### Frontend - Upload
#### [MODIFY] [Upload UI]
- Improve mobile responsiveness and add "Engagement Settings" (where users can see their boosted status).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Trigger `increment_view_count` and verify both `videos` and `daily_stats` are updated.
- Verify `/api/studio/analytics` returns correctly formatted data for Recharts.

### Manual Verification
- Check Dashboard on mobile emulator (390px).
- Verify "Slow Drip" execution via Supabase SQL editor.
